Abstract = {This study attempts to capture the experience teachers learnt in using
   an immersive virtual reality (VR) system known as the Cave Automatic
   Virtual Environment (CAVE) to facilitate students' learning. In this
   study, the development and facilitation of the learning and teaching
   activities, in particular the pedagogical strategies that make use of
   the immersive VR environment, are analysed using the Technological
   Pedagogical Content Knowledge (TPACK) framework and the specialised
