Abstract = {This paper proposes a design of a completely online course in a Chinese
   university and explores applying Technological Pedagogical Content
   Knowledge (TPACK) to facilitate this online course. The primary purpose
   of this study is to explore the potentials of applying TPACK to
   facilitate a completely online course and to build an effective online
   learning community in a comprehensive central south university in China.
   This paper primarily focuses on introducing the online course design and
   the online learning environment for the online course in a Chinese
   educational website, and then proposes the TPACK definition and relevant
   review of literature, online TPACK application principles and examples.
   This paper concludes with possibilities, potentials, and implications of
   transforming the teacher-centered pedagogy to student-centered social
