   Implications},
Booktitle = {DESIGN OF TECHNOLOGY-ENHANCED LEARNING: INTEGRATING RESEARCH AND
   PRACTICE},
Year = {2017},
Pages = {17-33},
Abstract = {This chapter introduces the Technology Pedagogy and Content Knowledge
   (TPACK) model as it relates to technology-enhanced learning design. The
   key features of the framework are unpacked, along with a brief
   examination of what TPACK looks like in practice. Approaches to
   developing TPACK capacity are considered, with learning-by-design
   emerging as the most promising technique. Issues relating to TPACK are
   also critically discussed, including those relating to measurement and
   the capacity of the framework to support educational design practice.},
